race.description: Spelling At Coolmore Mt White Handicap (Bm64)
race.comment: POINT SCORE (10) gets the nod in another tricky race. Copped some early trouble then raced ungenerously so his unplaced effort at Kembla last start is worth overlooking. Suited coming back in trip and did win at his only run on a heavy track. IN AND OUT (7) blew the kick and was never in contention when resuming over 1200m at Warwick Farm last time out. Ran a couple of nice races early last prep on rain-affected ground. Fitter and should give a good account. CLEAR PROOF (2) led and was brave in defeat at massive odds at Warwick Farm last start. Should give backers a sight again. SPACEBALLS (8) resumes. Better performed on top of the ground so keep an eye on the track conditions as the meeting progresses. In a modest affair can sneak into the frame. The interesting runner is the Waller-trained CONCORDIA WIND (3) who hasn't raced since winning at Rosehill in November 2024. Talented mare who must be respected if there is any market confidence.
